\section{Project Overview}

AutoMind AI is an AI-powered predictive maintenance platform for fleet operations. It combines a supervised machine learning model with an agentic AI recommendation engine to identify vehicles at risk of failure before breakdowns occur, enabling proactive and cost-effective maintenance scheduling.

The system is built as an interactive Streamlit web application and is designed for fleet managers who need real-time, data-driven maintenance decisions without requiring data science expertise.

\section{Problem Statement}

Unplanned equipment failures in industrial and commercial fleets result in costly downtime, safety hazards, and reactive maintenance cycles. Traditional maintenance schedules are time-based rather than condition-based, leading to either over-maintenance (wasted cost) or under-maintenance (unexpected failures).

This project addresses the problem by:

\begin{itemize}
    \item Predicting failure probability per vehicle using ML
    \item Categorizing vehicles into actionable risk tiers
    \item Generating context-aware maintenance recommendations via an LLM agent
\end{itemize}

\section{Dataset}

\textbf{Source:} AI4I 2020 Predictive Maintenance Dataset \\
\textbf{Size:} 10,001 machines $\times$ 14 features \\
\textbf{Failure Rate:} 3.39\%

\begin{longtable}{|p{5cm}|p{8cm}|}
\hline
\textbf{Feature} & \textbf{Description} \\
\hline
Type & Product variant (M / L / H) \\
\hline
Air temperature [K] & Ambient temperature \\
\hline
Process temperature [K] & Operating temperature \\
\hline
Rotational speed [rpm] & Spindle speed \\
\hline
Torque [Nm] & Applied torque \\
\hline
Tool wear [min] & Cumulative tool usage \\
\hline
TWF, HDF, PWF, OSF, RNF & Specific failure mode flags \\
\hline
Machine failure & Target label (0 / 1) \\
\hline
\end{longtable}

The dataset is stored in \texttt{Raw/ai4i2020.csv} and loads automatically at application startup.

